<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=5785&amp;p=35075#p35075"><![CDATA[
OK, so Pipalou50.<br />Je vous laisse le soin de traduire en français<br /><br />Added User Image to classic/7 style clrSharp2<br />Round, or square.<br />Can use transparent icon picture, when added to its &quot;User Picture&quot; location in the &quot;General Behavior&quot; tab.<br /><br />Added Text Shadow to classic/7 style clrSharp2<br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br />Edwards clrSharp2 skin/skin7 is so beautiful, <br />I hope I'm not offending him adding the text shadow.<br />I could never figure out how to make it look good with black text and text shadow.<br /><br />You can go into file, and edit for darker or lighter text shadow:<br /><br />[GLASS_SHADOW AND BLACK_TEXT]<br />Main_text_shadow_color=#D0D0D0,#D0D0D0,#FFFFFF,#FFFFFF <br /><br />to shadow lighter<br />Main_text_shadow_color=#FFFFFF,#FFFFFF,#FFFFFF,#FFFFFF <br /><br /><br /><br />Same with white text:<br /><br />[GLASS_SHADOW]<br />Main_text_shadow_color=#202020,#202020,#000000,#000000<br /><br />to shadow darker<br />Main_text_shadow_color=#000000,#000000,#000000,#000000<br /><br /><br /><br />I never tested new skin on Windows 7, where Glow is available. <br />There might be interaction when glow and text shadow both enabled?<br /><br />Not sure if I missed any mistakes? Let me know. <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_e_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=856">juniper7</a> — Tue Dec 19, 2017 3:17 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
