Pipalou50,<br />I think I know what you are talking about. <br />With no theme in Win7, you get very powerful white glow. Hard to read.<br /><br />It is best to turn off glow, unless you are using the &quot;Clearscreen Sharp&quot; theme by K-Johnson.<br /><br />The maker of this skin, John Edward, advises to turn on the &quot;Aero fix&quot; option.<br />This makes a now dark grey glow using theme, into softer glow blend behind text.<br /><br />All I have done is upgraded his skins to have newer features that CSM provides.<br />Like split buttons, better no icon control, 7 style extension. <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_e_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=856">juniper7</a> — Tue Apr 05, 2016 6:54 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
