<link href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=5785&amp;p=25614#p25614"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[clrSharp1 2 3 .skin &amp; .skin7 upgraded for CSM 4.2.5]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=5785&amp;p=25614#p25614"><![CDATA[
clrSharp1 2 3 .skin &amp; .skin7 upgraded for CSM 4.2.5<br /><br /><br /><br />I saw these CSM skins on Deviant, made by pioneer John Edward.<br /><br />clrSharp <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://johnedwa.deviantart.com/art/clrSharp-Classic-Shell-Skin-155201674">http://johnedwa.deviantart.com/art/clrS ... -155201674</a><!-- m --><br /><br />clrSharp2 <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://johnedwa.deviantart.com/art/clrSharp2-Glass-159425288">http://johnedwa.deviantart.com/art/clrS ... -159425288</a><!-- m -->   <br /><br />clrSharp3 Dual <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://johnedwa.deviantart.com/art/clrSHARP3-Dual-275666986">http://johnedwa.deviantart.com/art/clrS ... -275666986</a><!-- m --><br /><br />They needed to be updated to work properly with CSM 4.2.5 which I've done.<br /><br />He made them to go with &quot;Clearscreen Sharp&quot; theme on Windows 7.<br />They can work without the theme in Windows 10. There won't be text glow. <br /><br />Menu looks, are totally different between operating systems, some pleasant, some not.<br />Win 10 will boost the glass color and opacity blur.<br /><br />To reduce the residual non neutral glass color on Win10, do any, or all of these adjustments:<br />In Windows personalize settings-pick a dark grey color<br />In CSM settings-reduce &quot;Glass opacity&quot; in &quot;menu Look&quot; tab.<br />In CSM settings-change &quot;Override glass color&quot; in &quot;menu Look&quot; tab, to a dark grey/black.<br />In skin settings- turn on &quot;Reduce Glass Color&quot;<br /><br />To stop brief glass color flash around menu, turn off &quot;Main menu animation&quot; in &quot;Menu Look&quot; tab. <br /><br /><br /><br />Edit: I changed this post by getting rid of scrunched up icons screenshot. <br />It was too scary and it's fixed in this all in one skin zip. <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_e_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=856">juniper7</a> — Sun Mar 06, 2016 12:30 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
